subSubSection.paragraph:
This species is morphologically similar to 

A. adetos

except for the following characters:

Adult. Head
(
Figs 27–32
). Frons with 5–9 setae (n = 7). Male flagellomeres with bare internode evanescing after flagellomere X but slight constriction remaining in flagellomeres XI–XII (
Fig. 30
). Mouthparts: labrum with 6–8 short setae (n = 7); labellum with 8–10 strong setae (n = 9).
